: NEXT: Criteria


## My Criteria For The Ultimate Parser

- Maintainability of a normal library so I can do changes even years later.
- Error reporting with line and column position and code snippet.
- Reporting of **multiple** errors, so I can fix (all) errors at once.
- Unicode support (working on UTF-8 encoded Unicode code points instead of bytes if requested).
- Type safety (including filling arbitrary typed data) using generics.
- Idiomatic Go code.
- Support for binary input (including byte position and hex dump for errors).
- Good performance (for the feature set).

: NEXT: Starting The Quest

## Starting The Quest

- Some Go parser libraries or generators sport a really cool way of doing things.
- All are hobby projects.
- It's impossible to find something that can meet the more difficult criteria.
- So I looked beyond the Go universe.


